1
00:00:01,060 --> 00:00:03,060
(theme song)

2
00:00:03,060 --> 00:01:44,872
♪

3
00:01:46,038 --> 00:01:47,240
Mr. Saeke's been
conning people.

4
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,180
I am completely
aware of all that.

5
00:01:49,180 --> 00:01:50,160
Oh?

6
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:51,180
But there's more to it.

7
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:53,270
I'm sure this man
has much bigger plans.

8
00:01:53,270 --> 00:01:55,270
He's putting in a railroad,

9
00:01:55,270 --> 00:01:57,250
but it's not what
it seems to be.

10
00:01:57,250 --> 00:02:00,080
He's building a tunnel instead.

11
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:01,170
♪

12
00:02:01,170 --> 00:02:04,050
I am the head of
the water family.

13
00:02:04,050 --> 00:02:05,230
We want our ki back,

14
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:08,120
and nothing will stop us!

15
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,240
(laughing)

16
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:12,030
(grunting)

17
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:13,190
Enough!

18
00:02:13,190 --> 00:02:15,140
(snickers)

19
00:02:15,140 --> 00:02:17,210
(grunting)

20
00:02:17,210 --> 00:02:19,180
He's mine!

21
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:21,030
Take this!

22
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:22,120
Stop!

23
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:23,180
♪

24
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:24,070
No!

25
00:02:24,070 --> 00:02:25,020
(screams)

26
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,710
(grunting)

27
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:28,220
Huh?

28
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:29,260
Kori!

29
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:31,010
She's dying.

30
00:02:31,010 --> 00:02:32,060
(grunts)

31
00:02:32,060 --> 00:02:37,000
♪

32
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,190
It is time now.

33
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:39,220
Time for war.

34
00:02:39,220 --> 00:02:41,030
(thunder)

35
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:54,040
♪

36
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:57,220
(labored breathing)

37
00:02:57,220 --> 00:02:59,250
♪

38
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:13,150
Look at that.

39
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:15,120
(murmur of conversation)

40
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,010
♪

41
00:03:25,010 --> 00:03:26,200
Kori's leg looks bad.

42
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,140
It is bad.

43
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,070
Huh?

44
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:30,060
Reisui used
a Tang feng shui method

45
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:31,220
that he learned in China.

46
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:34,030
It causes her wounds
to absorb poisonous air

47
00:03:34,030 --> 00:03:35,230
which will make her body rot.

48
00:03:35,230 --> 00:03:37,080
It's a death that's terrible.

49
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:39,060
I've heard about this,
but because this method

50
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,200
has been banned in Japan,

51
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:43,130
I've never had the chance
to observe something like this.

52
00:03:43,130 --> 00:03:44,260
I don't understand it.

53
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:47,220
Why would anyone
want to be that cruel?

54
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:51,090
Mr. Jinpu, can Kori be cured?

55
00:03:51,090 --> 00:03:52,150
Yes.

56
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:54,090
The spring at Musashino.

57
00:03:54,090 --> 00:03:56,150
You're kidding me,
the same one?

58
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:57,120
Right.

59
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,040
Saeke's trying to build
that tunnel of his

60
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,250
to get that spring water.

61
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:02,100
It's very powerful.

62
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:04,110
The spring has been
filled with strong ki

63
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:06,000
ever since ancient times.

64
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,110
If used incorrectly,
it can be dangerous.

65
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:10,000
Saeke wants to exploit the ki

66
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,230
and use it for evil purposes.

67
00:04:12,230 --> 00:04:14,020
We need that water.

68
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,270
It's the only way
to save her.

69
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:17,250
Mr. Jinpu, we have
to move quickly.

70
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:20,280
Help me find the way
to the spring water.

71
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:22,190
It's very important
we get to that spring

72
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:24,040
before it's too late for her.

73
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,030
-Let's go!
-No!

74
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:26,010
Huh?

75
00:04:26,010 --> 00:04:28,120
Your job is to stay
here and protect Kori.

76
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,080
It could be
dangerous over there.

77
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:31,010
He's right.

78
00:04:31,010 --> 00:04:31,520
Huh?

79
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,060
It's better that way.

80
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:34,180
She shouldn't be alone.

81
00:04:34,180 --> 00:04:38,000
♪

82
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,030
Mm.

83
00:04:39,030 --> 00:04:43,070
♪

84
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:44,120
We should leave now.

85
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:46,070
I want to get the
troops ready to move.

86
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,100
Right.

87
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,110
Good luck, men.

88
00:04:48,110 --> 00:04:50,020
We hope that you will succeed.

89
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:52,250
♪

90
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:54,250
Chief, tell Kawaji
to order his men

91
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:56,210
to find Saeke and lock him up.

92
00:04:56,210 --> 00:04:58,020
We need some hard evidence.

93
00:04:58,020 --> 00:04:59,020
Yes, sir.

94
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:03,020
This is the police!

95
00:05:03,020 --> 00:05:04,260
I'll try upstairs, sir!

96
00:05:04,260 --> 00:05:06,010
Look!

97
00:05:06,010 --> 00:05:08,180
What a mess.

98
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:10,060
There's nothin' here, sir.

99
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:11,190
Not a soul, sir!

100
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:14,010
Sir, they must have known
that we were coming.

101
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:15,260
That is becoming rather obvious.

102
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,290
Huh?

103
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:18,070
We have to bring in Saeke

104
00:05:18,070 --> 00:05:19,250
no matter what the cost,

105
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:22,090
even if we have to
bring in reinforcements.

106
00:05:22,090 --> 00:05:24,010
Yes, sir!

107
00:05:24,010 --> 00:05:26,010
Saeke doesn't need
this dojo anymore.

108
00:05:26,010 --> 00:05:27,260
He has bigger fish to fry.

109
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:29,290
I doubt that there's
any danger of attack,

110
00:05:29,290 --> 00:05:33,070
so I need you two to do
something while we're gone.

111
00:05:33,070 --> 00:05:34,160
What do you mean?

112
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:36,060
Just this.

113
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:38,120
Saeke wants to destroy
our jin completely,

114
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,280
and he's building
up his own now.

115
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:43,030
I don't know how much
jin he has in place,

116
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:43,892
but I need you to look

117
00:05:43,892 --> 00:05:46,040
for every one of
his centers of power.

118
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,120
And destroy them?

119
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:49,250
Is there some kind of sign
we should be looking for?

120
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:51,170
There should be
a symbol on each spot

121
00:05:51,170 --> 00:05:53,090
that takes the form of a demon.

122
00:05:53,090 --> 00:05:55,250
It represents
the Yurakimon Gate.

123
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,220
Mm-hm.

124
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:01,220
We're gonna be
counting on you two.

125
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,220
(labored breathing)

126
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:30,100
Hm, Jinpu.

127
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:33,140
His name sounds similar
to that of the wind family.

128
00:06:33,140 --> 00:06:35,000
Could it be?

129
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,050
Hm.

130
00:06:36,050 --> 00:06:39,110
He must be one of the last
of them alive on Earth.

131
00:06:39,110 --> 00:06:41,230
If he is, then it's
going to be a problem.

132
00:06:41,230 --> 00:06:42,290
Dammit.

133
00:06:42,290 --> 00:06:45,220
We didn't plan on one of our
enemies getting in the way.

134
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:46,240
But don't worry,

135
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,080
we're sure to get rid of him

136
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,200
without any trouble.

137
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,210
Terrific.

138
00:06:50,210 --> 00:06:53,010
I'm counting on you, my friend.

139
00:06:53,010 --> 00:06:54,070
Come here.

140
00:06:54,070 --> 00:06:58,200
♪

141
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:01,090
This is my plan,
so listen carefully.

142
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:02,250
We've destroyed
most of their jin,

143
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:04,290
but a few key targets remain.

144
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:06,270
We destroyed
the Ministry of Construction

145
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:09,080
using the energy that we
acquired from the restaurant

146
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:10,210
and the Kamiya dojo.

147
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:13,200
It's imperative that we
completely obliterate their jin.

148
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:16,050
To accomplish this goal,
we must manipulate the ki

149
00:07:16,050 --> 00:07:19,000
to the northeastern
section of Musashino.

150
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,200
But before we do that,
we have to liberate the flow

151
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:23,160
from several strategic points.

152
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:26,250
Our next objective is to
destroy the Judicial Ministry

153
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:28,260
and the police department.

154
00:07:28,260 --> 00:07:31,060
Ten Ruin is the final target.

155
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,851
That's what we decided, right?

156
00:07:32,851 --> 00:07:33,712
That's right.

157
00:07:33,712 --> 00:07:35,140
The building itself
is situated

158
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:36,280
on an important power point

159
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:39,090
in Tokugawa's
original jin formation.

160
00:07:39,090 --> 00:07:42,190
He had deliberately designed
it to protect the city.

161
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:45,170
A cabinet meeting will be
held next week at that site.

162
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:47,250
High ranking officials
are scheduled to be there.

163
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:51,010
If we destroy it, we'll get
rid of all of them at once.

164
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:54,010
Then, the obliteration of
Tokugawa's jin will be complete,

165
00:07:54,010 --> 00:07:55,200
and we can start our takeover.

166
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,240
We'll be in perfect position.

167
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,200
The destruction of Iguno jin

168
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,240
and the opportunity
to build a new formation

169
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,170
is our only goal.

170
00:08:03,170 --> 00:08:05,110
Once we bump off
all those officials,

171
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:07,140
we'll be able to
take over the country.

172
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:09,260
It's all very simple.

173
00:08:09,260 --> 00:08:11,130
So you're absolutely positive

174
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:12,290
that those officials
will be there?

175
00:08:12,290 --> 00:08:15,230
I'm sure; I've got these
politicians under my thumb.

176
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:17,110
They've all been
handsomely paid off,

177
00:08:17,110 --> 00:08:19,020
so it shouldn't be a problem.

178
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:20,040
(laughs)

179
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,170
It's going to be
well worth the money

180
00:08:21,170 --> 00:08:22,280
to watch them all die.

181
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:25,000
That stupid Meiji government.

182
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,030
How do they expect to change

183
00:08:26,030 --> 00:08:28,290
when they're still relying
on the jin of the past?

184
00:08:28,290 --> 00:08:31,010
The building is on
a main point of jin.

185
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,040
That's a mistake.

186
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:34,220
It would eventually
destroy them anyway.

187
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:38,040
Oh well, I guess we'll just have
to speed up the process a bit.

188
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:40,070
They'll find out
how scary we are.

189
00:08:40,070 --> 00:08:42,050
That will make it much more fun.

190
00:08:42,050 --> 00:08:45,190
(evil laughter)

191
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:49,080
♪

192
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,080
(chanting)

193
00:08:51,080 --> 00:09:29,090
♪

194
00:09:31,290 --> 00:09:32,260
(grunting)

195
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:40,230
(thunder)

196
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:49,160
(screaming)

197
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:56,140
(grunting)

198
00:09:56,140 --> 00:10:03,020
♪

199
00:10:03,020 --> 00:10:05,200
(indistinct conversation)

200
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,240
It's a demon.

201
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,190
Which means that
it's a point of jin.

202
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:10,090
We have to get
over there and stop it.

203
00:10:10,090 --> 00:10:13,180
Heh, I don't exactly
specialize in manual labor,

204
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:14,210
but I'll try.

205
00:10:14,210 --> 00:10:15,290
Out of my way, move!

206
00:10:15,290 --> 00:10:17,170
I've got some jin to crush.

207
00:10:17,170 --> 00:10:20,010
♪

208
00:10:20,010 --> 00:10:21,210
Just as I expected!

209
00:10:21,210 --> 00:10:23,210
(grunting)

210
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:36,170
♪

211
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,230
Huh.

212
00:10:38,230 --> 00:10:41,110
Is he a man or a monkey?

213
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:42,260
♪

214
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:49,260
Oh...

215
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:52,050
Oh, I can't believe it.

216
00:10:52,050 --> 00:10:54,270
The police department
is completely demolished.

217
00:10:54,270 --> 00:10:57,100
This makes no sense at all.

218
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:58,180
Hm--huh?

219
00:10:58,180 --> 00:11:00,280
Stop your moaning, Chief.

220
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:02,290
I'm telling you, knock it off!

221
00:11:02,290 --> 00:11:03,150
Huh?

222
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,160
You get up from there.

223
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,000
But, sir, can't you see

224
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,240
the police department's
been destroyed!

225
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:09,120
There's nothing
left but some rubble.

226
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:11,240
Stupid, I'm not blind,
I can see that!

227
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,210
So what happened with
your investigation?

228
00:11:13,210 --> 00:11:14,250
We don't know.

229
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:16,180
So far, nobody in his company's

230
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:19,190
been able to tell us
where Mr. Saeke is, sir.

231
00:11:19,190 --> 00:11:22,110
Well, step up your
efforts and find that guy.

232
00:11:22,110 --> 00:11:24,200
All other investigations
are to be put on hold.

233
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,160
Let's get that bastard.

234
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:34,180
A spring of ki is actually
flowing beneath the ground?

235
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:37,150
It's hard to believe there
is such a thing in Kanto.

236
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:39,060
Tokugawa was extremely fortunate

237
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:41,040
to base his
headquarters here in Edo.

238
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:45,010
This land is literally flowing
with a positive ki force.

239
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:47,100
If you think about it,
that's one of the main reasons

240
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:51,140
the Tokugawa Era lasted
for well over 300 years.

241
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:52,140
Hm.

242
00:11:52,140 --> 00:11:56,230
♪

243
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:58,210
Tell me, Jinpu,
do you think it's possible

244
00:11:58,210 --> 00:12:00,200
Reisui intentionally hurt Kori

245
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:03,050
so they could lure us
to Musashino and trap us?

246
00:12:03,050 --> 00:12:04,290
♪

247
00:12:04,290 --> 00:12:07,180
Although it doesn't really
matter if they did or not.

248
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:10,010
I'll do anything
I can to save her life.

249
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:11,110
Listen to me.

250
00:12:11,110 --> 00:12:12,240
When Commander Perry came,

251
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:14,190
I was married to a woman.

252
00:12:14,190 --> 00:12:17,080
One day I woke up and
found out she'd left me.

253
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,130
She was unhappy with the fact

254
00:12:18,130 --> 00:12:21,070
that I was so
dedicated to feng shui.

255
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:23,190
I was never able to have
children because of it,

256
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:26,000
so there's no one
to carry on my name.

257
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,210
Ever since I met you, I felt
as though you were like me,

258
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:29,290
but I guess you're not.

259
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:31,240
I was too immersed
in my vocation

260
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:35,200
and didn't realize
I was losing her.

261
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,240
(sighs)

262
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:40,040
So Kenshin,
I made a big mistake,

263
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,130
and I can't make up
for my mistakes,

264
00:12:42,130 --> 00:12:44,250
but you still have the
chance to do what's right.

265
00:12:44,250 --> 00:12:46,120
Sorry, Jinpu.

266
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:49,020
You really must
cherish her, Kenshin.

267
00:12:49,020 --> 00:12:51,020
If you're constantly obsessed
with what you're doing,

268
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,210
you'll become like me,

269
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:54,280
and you don't want to be.

270
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:56,260
The days of the
sword toting samurai

271
00:12:56,260 --> 00:12:58,250
ended with the Tokugawa Era.

272
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,250
Feng shui will end as well.

273
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:02,230
We have to learn to
put the past behind us

274
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:05,220
and look forward to the future.

275
00:13:05,220 --> 00:13:07,120
It'll make us happier.

276
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:09,110
Well, sir, ever
since the destruction

277
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:11,060
of the Ministry of Construction,

278
00:13:11,060 --> 00:13:13,050
the judiciary,
and the police department,

279
00:13:13,050 --> 00:13:15,060
swarms of people
have left the city.

280
00:13:15,060 --> 00:13:17,190
So far, we have been
unable to secure the area

281
00:13:17,190 --> 00:13:20,140
and prevent any more
damage to public buildings.

282
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:22,160
We need more manpower.

283
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:23,180
What?

284
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:25,050
Deploy all battalions.

285
00:13:25,050 --> 00:13:26,170
I want each and
every one of them

286
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:28,200
assembled and prepared to march.

287
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,000
Every one of them?

288
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,050
But that's a lot of men.

289
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:32,160
We have no choice.

290
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,060
I want them to
head for Musashino

291
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:36,240
and destroy Saeke's
railroad construction area.

292
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,180
He has got to be stopped.

293
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:40,190
By the way,
I'll be leading the attack,

294
00:13:40,190 --> 00:13:41,250
so let's get going.

295
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:52,160
♪

296
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:54,160
(grunting)

297
00:13:54,160 --> 00:14:01,130
♪

298
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:03,110
Ah...

299
00:14:03,110 --> 00:14:05,020
Those men never stop.

300
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:07,110
Tsunan told me he's got
men working double shifts.

301
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:09,000
We can't avoid them.

302
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,090
We can't afford to wait.

303
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:12,080
There just isn't
much time left.

304
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,250
Yes, you're right.

305
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:16,080
I'm afraid we'll just
have to take a chance.

306
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:17,110
Are you ready?

307
00:14:17,110 --> 00:14:18,210
Sure, let's go.

308
00:14:21,140 --> 00:14:22,230
♪

309
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:26,180
(panting)

310
00:14:26,180 --> 00:14:28,060
(shouting)

311
00:14:28,060 --> 00:14:30,170
(screaming)

312
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:32,030
♪

313
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:33,060
I'll take care of this.

314
00:14:33,060 --> 00:14:35,050
Jin, go back!

315
00:14:35,050 --> 00:14:38,190
(grunting)

316
00:14:38,190 --> 00:14:39,250
Let's go!

317
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:42,040
♪

318
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:43,180
I'm here from
the police department.

319
00:14:43,180 --> 00:14:46,050
I need to see
Yamagata right away.

320
00:14:46,050 --> 00:14:48,040
Well, he's out of
his office right now.

321
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:50,030
Perhaps I could help you?
What's the matter, sir?

322
00:14:50,030 --> 00:14:52,030
Our building has
gone up in smoke,

323
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:54,100
so we need you to
give us some space.

324
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:55,190
Uh, that's impossible.

325
00:14:55,190 --> 00:14:57,050
We have no extra space here.

326
00:14:57,050 --> 00:14:58,220
Then make some,
and hurry it up!

327
00:14:58,220 --> 00:15:00,260
Follow me, men!

328
00:15:00,260 --> 00:15:01,270
(maniacal laughter)

329
00:15:01,270 --> 00:15:03,130
So where's that spring?

330
00:15:03,130 --> 00:15:05,200
Keep running,
it's in the back.

331
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,100
Jin!

332
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,160
(speaking foreign language)

333
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:10,040
(screaming)

334
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,190
(creaking)

335
00:15:11,190 --> 00:15:12,270
Huh?

336
00:15:12,270 --> 00:15:15,280
♪

337
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:17,070
Oh no.

338
00:15:17,070 --> 00:15:26,090
♪

339
00:15:26,090 --> 00:15:27,150
What was that?

340
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:29,220
They must have put a special
kind of jin in this tunnel

341
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:31,210
to keep us from trespassing.

342
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:33,050
It reacts to my technique

343
00:15:33,050 --> 00:15:35,230
and then it retaliates
automatically.

344
00:15:35,230 --> 00:15:37,100
It acts like a mirror.

345
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:40,190
Well, how are we gonna
stop it from doing that?

346
00:15:40,190 --> 00:15:43,030
I have a plan.

347
00:15:43,030 --> 00:15:45,080
We'll get there,
don't you worry.

348
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:50,210
♪

349
00:15:50,210 --> 00:15:51,270
There's another one.

350
00:15:51,270 --> 00:15:53,180
It's got the face of a demon.

351
00:15:53,180 --> 00:15:55,100
Hey, they know we're here
and they're after us.

352
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:57,020
Be careful, Sanosuke.

353
00:15:57,020 --> 00:15:58,180
(grunting)

354
00:15:58,180 --> 00:16:00,060
(maniacal laughter)

355
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:01,240
(grunting)

356
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,020
Go for it!

357
00:16:03,020 --> 00:16:05,250
♪

358
00:16:05,250 --> 00:16:07,050
Thanks, pal!

359
00:16:07,050 --> 00:16:08,160
(grunting)

360
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:15,010
♪

361
00:16:15,010 --> 00:16:17,000
When will we get
to the spring, Jinpu?

362
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,170
We should be there soon.

363
00:16:18,170 --> 00:16:22,160
♪

364
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:23,240
It keeps going.

365
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:25,000
I know.

366
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,290
But we can't stop now.

367
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:28,260
(panting)

368
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,050
Huh?

369
00:16:34,030 --> 00:16:37,000
♪

370
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,040
It's all blocked.

371
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,080
We've come to a dead end.

372
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:41,090
How are we gonna
find the spring?

373
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:42,280
That five point
star is being used

374
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,270
to protect the spring
against enemies.

375
00:16:44,270 --> 00:16:47,170
The spring is
probably behind it.

376
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:48,060
Hm.

377
00:16:48,060 --> 00:16:50,000
Hm?

378
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,200
The power of the ki
is very strong.

379
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:55,160
It may have the
potential to be dangerous.

380
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:58,030
He has purposely directed
the energy flow to the spring,

381
00:16:58,030 --> 00:17:00,230
making the ki capable
of doing damage.

382
00:17:00,230 --> 00:17:02,170
I just hope I'm wrong.

383
00:17:02,170 --> 00:17:04,120
Saeke must be planning
a major attack

384
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:07,010
as a means to take
over the government.

385
00:17:07,010 --> 00:17:08,230
Mm-hm.

386
00:17:08,230 --> 00:17:10,030
I'm sure.

387
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:11,010
Wait.

388
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:12,280
This doesn't make
much sense to me.

389
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:15,020
It's quite a distance
between here and the city.

390
00:17:15,020 --> 00:17:17,190
The power will decrease
by the time it gets there.

391
00:17:17,190 --> 00:17:19,090
Still, we can't take a chance

392
00:17:19,090 --> 00:17:22,080
of letting something
that disastrous happen.

393
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:23,250
It's monstrous.

394
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:27,080
♪

395
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:28,270
So what do you plan to do now?

396
00:17:28,270 --> 00:17:30,050
Just one thing.

397
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:31,012
What?

398
00:17:31,012 --> 00:17:32,180
Destroy the star.

399
00:17:32,180 --> 00:17:34,160
I thought you said
your feng shui technique

400
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:36,060
doesn't work
inside this tunnel.

401
00:17:36,060 --> 00:17:37,210
If we want to obtain the water,

402
00:17:37,210 --> 00:17:38,260
we must try,

403
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:40,090
so move out of the way

404
00:17:40,090 --> 00:17:42,100
and get ready for anything.

405
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:43,200
What do you want me to do?

406
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:45,150
You keep the jin men away.

407
00:17:45,150 --> 00:17:46,170
♪

408
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:47,260
Right, ready.

409
00:17:47,260 --> 00:17:49,260
♪

410
00:17:49,260 --> 00:17:51,260
(chanting)

411
00:17:51,260 --> 00:18:10,000
♪

412
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,000
(gasps)

413
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,000
♪

414
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,210
(screaming)

415
00:18:14,210 --> 00:18:15,180
(grunting)

416
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:22,040
♪

417
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,170
You must be in pain.

418
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:28,100
(screaming)

419
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:30,000
(maniacal laughter)

420
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,000
Looks like there's more of them.

421
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:32,921
Huh?

422
00:18:32,921 --> 00:18:33,742
Huh?

423
00:18:33,742 --> 00:18:34,682
Watch out!

424
00:18:34,682 --> 00:18:36,010
Huh?

425
00:18:36,010 --> 00:18:40,230
♪

426
00:18:40,230 --> 00:18:42,060
(commotion)

427
00:18:42,060 --> 00:18:43,000
(screaming)

428
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,010
Oh!

429
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,130
What's that?

430
00:18:46,130 --> 00:18:47,030
This is bad.

431
00:18:47,030 --> 00:18:48,070
The ki is beginning to flow

432
00:18:48,070 --> 00:18:50,190
in a spiral pattern
against the wall.

433
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:53,050
Ki energy is only
beneficial to the world

434
00:18:53,050 --> 00:18:55,020
if it flows in a straight line.

435
00:18:55,020 --> 00:18:57,130
When it does,
it's peaceful and harmonious,

436
00:18:57,130 --> 00:18:59,060
but once it starts to spiral,

437
00:18:59,060 --> 00:19:01,260
the speed increases and
it becomes too powerful.

438
00:19:01,260 --> 00:19:04,010
Then it becomes unpredictable.

439
00:19:04,010 --> 00:19:06,200
The violence it creates
cannot be tamed.

440
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,230
This mighty force

441
00:19:07,230 --> 00:19:11,210
can turn into an evil
weapon of destruction.

442
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:14,130
But, Jinpu, this is big trouble.

443
00:19:14,130 --> 00:19:17,040
What if the ki spirals
from Musashino to the city?

444
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:18,190
Ah?

445
00:19:18,190 --> 00:19:19,180
Huh?

446
00:19:19,180 --> 00:19:21,000
(growling)

447
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,050
Looks like those pests
want a little more.

448
00:19:24,050 --> 00:19:25,200
I think I know how
to get rid of them,

449
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:28,110
but I'll have to use
chizumi no jin,

450
00:19:28,110 --> 00:19:29,230
so stand back.

451
00:19:29,230 --> 00:19:31,100
It could hurt you.

452
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:33,010
♪

453
00:19:33,010 --> 00:19:34,150
It's much too strong.

454
00:19:34,150 --> 00:19:36,180
Yes, but if I put
my body into it,

455
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:38,100
then it will calm
down the ki flow.

456
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:39,220
That may be able to stop it.

457
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:41,230
(shrieking)

458
00:19:41,230 --> 00:19:42,260
(grunting)

459
00:19:42,260 --> 00:19:44,230
(shouting chant)

460
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:51,260
Take my energy and settle down.

461
00:19:51,260 --> 00:19:56,060
♪

462
00:19:56,060 --> 00:20:00,010
Feel my positive energy
calling to you and be still!

463
00:20:05,030 --> 00:20:07,090
Huh?

464
00:20:07,090 --> 00:20:09,260
Oh!

465
00:20:09,260 --> 00:20:11,060
Oh...

466
00:20:14,050 --> 00:20:16,020
(soft otherworldly sounds)

467
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:20,220
Calm your spiraling flow.

468
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:23,280
Don't be persuaded by the water
family's plan of corruption.

469
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:26,250
Stay on the course
of harmony and peace.

470
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,150
(soft otherworldly sounds)

471
00:20:32,150 --> 00:20:34,190
Oh no!

472
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:35,200
A crack.

473
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,190
The force of the flow
is just too powerful.

474
00:20:38,190 --> 00:20:41,060
(cracking)

475
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:42,120
What's gonna happen now?

476
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,200
It's coming!

477
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,170
Ah!

478
00:20:46,270 --> 00:20:48,160
The tunnel's not
able to support it.

479
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:51,050
We have to get out.

480
00:20:51,050 --> 00:20:52,200
You can do it!

481
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:54,200
Take the water.

482
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,280
Come on!

483
00:21:08,060 --> 00:21:10,150
Ah...

484
00:21:10,150 --> 00:21:11,170
Enough.

485
00:21:11,170 --> 00:21:14,190
We have to save the rest
to help Kori get better.

486
00:21:14,190 --> 00:21:15,270
I hope you're right about that.

487
00:21:15,270 --> 00:21:17,060
Sir, sir!

488
00:21:17,060 --> 00:21:18,280
Good news!

489
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:22,020
I found them, they both made
it out of there and survived.

490
00:21:22,020 --> 00:21:24,220
They look ragged
but they're all right.

491
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:31,210
♪

492
00:21:31,210 --> 00:21:33,020
We have to get back.

493
00:21:33,020 --> 00:21:34,020
We'll make sure that you do,

494
00:21:34,020 --> 00:21:35,100
so don't worry about it.

495
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:36,250
Has the problem been solved?

496
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:37,270
No, in fact,

497
00:21:37,270 --> 00:21:39,280
it's more serious
that we thought it was.

498
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:41,210
Just what do you mean?

499
00:21:41,210 --> 00:21:43,000
The tunnel's gone,

500
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,210
but the ki has been
released to the northeast.

501
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:49,000
Yes, our work at Musashino
has been successful,

502
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,030
and those two idiots
just saved us the trouble

503
00:21:51,030 --> 00:21:52,170
of doing it ourselves.

504
00:21:52,170 --> 00:21:56,080
Well, we'll need to make certain
they don't bother us again.

505
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:58,140
Usui, I will make
the journey north

506
00:21:58,140 --> 00:22:00,060
and follow the ki's path.

507
00:22:00,060 --> 00:22:02,100
You stay here and
take care of the city.

508
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:04,150
Yes, that's the plan
I had in mind.

509
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:07,060
The ki has started to
move at a rapid pace.

510
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:09,200
No one is capable
of stopping it now.

511
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:12,020
♪

512
00:22:12,020 --> 00:22:13,063
What's that?

513
00:22:13,063 --> 00:22:13,983
Are you trying to tell me

514
00:22:13,983 --> 00:22:15,270
we have absolutely no control?

515
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:17,060
Because the ki's spiraling,

516
00:22:17,060 --> 00:22:19,150
it'll be hard to aim it
into the right spot.

517
00:22:19,150 --> 00:22:22,040
They need to develop a
strategy to harness it.

518
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:25,000
We have to outmaneuver
their jin to beat them.

519
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:28,050
That means we'll have to
follow the path of the ki.

520
00:22:28,050 --> 00:22:30,070
Which direction is it
heading right now?

521
00:22:30,070 --> 00:22:33,260
It's heading northeast
right into the next town,

522
00:22:33,260 --> 00:22:35,070
the town of Nikko.

523
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:38,130
♪

524
00:22:38,130 --> 00:22:39,100
Nikko.

525
00:22:40,651 --> 00:22:42,210
(theme song)

526
00:22:42,210 --> 00:25:03,190
♪

527
00:25:04,220 --> 00:25:07,150
♪

